President Trump delivered remarks at the Harris Conference Center in Charlotte, North Carolina, where he signed an executive order to extend retirement savings accounts to American workers employed at small businesses. The order aims to reduce regulatory barriers and allow small businesses to band together to create low-cost association retirement plans. The President emphasized the importance of providing retirement security to all Americans and highlighted the success of the economy, including low unemployment rates for various demographics. He also discussed the renegotiation of trade deals and his commitment to putting American workers first.